
---


@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes

class User {
  +String id : unique
  +String name
  +String email
  +Date dob
}

class Account {
  +String accountNumber : unique (auto-generated)
  +AccountType type
  +User user : 1
}

enum AccountType {
  Personal
  Business
}

class BusinessAccount {
  +String companyName
  +BigDecimal monthlyFee
}

class PersonalAccount {
  +List<FriendRequest> sentRequests
  +List<FriendRequest> receivedRequests
}

class FriendRequest {
  +PersonalAccount requester
  +PersonalAccount recipient
  +RequestStatus status
}

enum RequestStatus {
  Pending
  Accepted
  Rejected
}

class Page {
  +String pageName : unique within an account
  +int visits
  +Account admin : 1
  +List<Privilege> privileges
}

class Privilege {
  +Page page
  +User user
  +PrivilegeLevel level
}

enum PrivilegeLevel {
  WriteOnWall
  AdjustInfo
  ManageContent
}

class AdvertisementPage {
  +double bounceRate
  +double clickThroughRate
  +double conversionRate
}

' Inheritance and associations

User "1" -- "0..*" Account : owns
Account "1" -- "0..*" Page : administers
Account <|-- BusinessAccount
Account <|-- PersonalAccount

BusinessAccount "1" -- "0..*" AdvertisementPage : creates
AdvertisementPage "1" -- "1" Page : extends

PersonalAccount "1" -- "0..*" FriendRequest : sends
PersonalAccount "1" -- "0..*" FriendRequest : receives

User "1" -- "0..*" Privilege : has
Page "1" -- "0..*" Privilege : grants

' Constraints

note right of User
  A user can only have one account.
end note

note right of Account
  Each account is uniquely identified by an account number.
end note

note right of BusinessAccount
  Must specify company name and pays a monthly fee.
end note

note right of PersonalAccount
  Can send/receive friend requests.
end note

note right of Page
  Must be administered by exactly one account.
  No two pages with same name under the same account.
end note

note right of AdvertisementPage
  Only created by business accounts.
  Tracks performance metrics.
end note

@enduml

---

### 📌 Notes on the Design:

- **User → Account**: One-to-zero-or-one relationship due to ToU restrictions.
- **Account** is abstract; **PersonalAccount** and **BusinessAccount** inherit from it.
- **FriendRequest** is exclusive to **PersonalAccounts**.
- **Page** is managed by one **Account**, and users can be granted **Privileges** to other pages.
- **AdvertisementPage** extends **Page** and includes analytics fields specific to marketing.

